{
  "texts": [
    "This may be because the number of impurity phases in the training images was only six, and the training was insufficient.",
    "Region (V) in Fig. 4a has a peaked superconducting phase in the void deeper than the image cross-section ('submarine ridge'); the brightness is relatively high due to the secondary electron image feature.",
    "Consequently, the ridge is misidentified by the thresholding methods and U-Net model.",
    "However, among the FCN models, FCN-8s segmented properly.",
    "This is because FCN-8s incorporate more global features than U-Net."
  ]
}